udy of her work to date.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion pictureszFrance. 0aWomen motion picture producers and directorszFrance. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aChocolat.  aClaire Denis.  aFrance's auteur.  acolonial Africa.  adialogue-based cinema.  aexile.  afictional feature films.  aforeignness.  aheterosexuals.  ahomosexuals.  amisappropriation.  aoppression.  apopular production.  aracism.  atransgression.1 aBeugnet, Martine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614125540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141255423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141255/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles